article.headline: New Hampshire 67, Iona 52
article.story: NEW ROCHELLE, N.Y. (AP) -- Mike Christensen scored 15 points and New Hampshire overcame an eight-point first-half deficit to beat winless Iona 67-52 on Friday night. Blagoj Janev added 13 points and Jermaine Anderson had 11 and Tyrece Gibbs 10 for the Wildcats (2-8), who snapped a four-game losing streak. Dexter Gray, a junior transfer from St. John's playing his second game for the Gaels (0-10), scored a career-high 20 points. The only other winless team in NCAA Division I is Delaware (0-8). The Gaels are off to the worst start in their 62 seasons of intercollegiate basketball. The 10 losses is their longest losing streak since closing the 1974-75 season with 15 straight losses. Iona led 19-11 after Gray scored with 12:24 left in the first half, but Christensen had 11 points to propel New Hampshire to a 42-34 halftime lead. The Gaels, who shot 25.8 percent from the field in the second half, never got closer than 46-40 after Justin Marshall scored with 16:18 left in the game. Marshall and Anthony Bruin each scored eight points for Iona. The Wildcats were 9-of-23 from 3-point range while the Gaels were 1-of-8.
